Explanation:

We iterate through the string word from the beginning to three characters before the end. For each iteration, we check if the characters at the current position and the next position are the same. If they are, we increment the count and move to the next character. We continue this process until we either find a mismatch or reach the end of the string. After iterating through the string, we return the maximum count found. This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because we only iterate through the string once, and a space complexity of O(1) as we only use a constant amount of space to store the count.

